    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe order of callback `BufReadPost` and 'LspAttach' is different on the second buffer opening.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nIn `.nvim.lua`:\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({\"BufNewFile\", \"BufReadPost\"}, {\n    callback = function(args)\n\t\tprint(\"Disable Formatting\")\n\t\tvim.b[args.buf].disable_formatting = true\n    end,\n}\n```\nin `init.lua`:\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('LspAttach', {\n  callback = function(args)\n    local c = vim.lsp.get_client_by_id(args.data.client_id)\n    if not c then return end\n    if vim.bo.filetype ~= \"lua\" and not vim.b.disable_formatting then\n      print(\"Autoformat\")\n      vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufWritePre', {\n        buffer = args.buf,\n        callback = function()\n          vim.lsp.buf.format({ bufnr = args.buf, id = c.id })\n        end,\n      })\n    end\n  end,\n});\n```\n\nWhen I enter 1st cpp file in messages I got:\n```\nDisable Formatting\n```\nWhen I enter 2nd cpp file in messages I got:\n```\nAutoformat\nDisable Formatting\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSame order of callbacks execution\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.3\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nclangd 19.1.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
